sec.p:
In the present approach, defect nucleation is supposed to require a certain amount of plastic deformation. One can thus distinguish at least two steps in the process of ductile damage:


the sound (undamaged) material behaves in elastic-viscoplastic manner and its response may be described using the J2-flow theory, i.e., via a Huber–Mises type yield criterion;

once defects nucleate and begin to grow, the (damaged) material may be considered as microporous and its response becomes pressure dependent.
